main.game.object

Class GameObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.game.object.GameObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Champion, Minion, Spell

    public class GameObject
extends java.lang.Object
    GameObject is the basis for every entity in the game that has to move, or has animations, or has health.
    Version:
    17 sep. 2015
    Author:
    ikhebgeenaccount

      • setAnimationType

        public void setAnimationType(int type)
        Sets the animation type, which decided what animation is played. Depending on what type of GameObject this is, (Minion, Champion, etc...) the animation that will be played depends on the constants in the class of the extension of GameObject (Minion, etc...).
        Parameters:
        type - The type of animation that needs to be played.

      • addAnimation

        public void addAnimation(int type,
                         java.awt.image.BufferedImage animationSprite,
                         int sceneLength)
        Adds an animation with default width of 50 pixels and default height of 100 pixels
        Parameters:
        type - The type of animation this is, corresponds to a constant in a subclass of GameObject, such as Minion.
        animationSprite - The image containing all frames of the animation.
        sceneLength - The length of one scene in milliseconds.

      • blink

        public boolean blink(NavMesh navMesh,
                     boolean movedLeft,
                     int distanceX)
        Checks if this GameObject can teleport specified distance in specified direction. If moving to the destination is not allowed, it checks for valid locations between destination and departure point with an interval of 25 pixels. If it finds a valid place, the GameObject moves there. Returns true if it moved, otherwise false.
        Parameters:
        navMesh - NavMesh on which the blinking happens.
        movedLeft - Decides the direction in which the blinking happens, false for right, true for left.
        distanceX - The distance that has to be traveled.
        Returns:
        boolean moved
